Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat, add a knob of @?butter{1%knob} too (if you have some). Add the onion, cook until really soft, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir regularly.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop the carrots on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, set aside.

Put the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} in a #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pull the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Peel the @garlic cloves{2}. Put one of the cloves into a square of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{}. Scrunch to enclose it.

Grate the rest of the garlic (or use a #garlic press{}). Roast the carrots on the top shelf of your oven until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Halfway through cooking, turn the carrots and add the garlic parcel to the tray for the final ~{10-12%minutes}.

Add the grated garlic to the softened onion along with the @ground cumin{1}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour the @water{240}(for the bulgur) into the saucepan with the onion, bring to the boil. Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10} and @bulgur wheat{120}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}, pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Put the @pasanda style seasoning{1} into a bowl and add the @olive oil{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} to the bowl and use your hands to coat the chicken in the spice.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Once the pan is hot, lay the chicken in the pan skin-side down and fry until golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn the chicken and cook for another ~{3-4%minutes}. Pop the chicken on the tray next to the carrots and roast until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Once cooked, add the @mango chutney{40} to the chicken. Turn to coat the chicken in the chutney. Set the tray aside.

== Rainbow Veg Side ==

When the chicken has 5 mins left to cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in your frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @baby corn, greens & carrots{200} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Then add a splash of @water{}, cover with a #lid{} (or some foil) and steam-fry until the veggies are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

== Assembly ==

Once cooked, remove the carrots from the oven. Carefully remove the garlic from the parcel, roughly chop or mash with a #fork{}. Stir the roasted garlic into the yoghurt.

Stir half the mint into the bulgur wheat and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice the chicken on a #cutting board{}. Spoon the bulgur wheat into bowls and top with the chicken and carrots. Spoon over any remaining chicken juices and the garlic yoghurt. Sprinkle over the remaining mint. Serve with the rainbow veg alongside and enjoy!